+# PR 214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated-hunk suggestion
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Code Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: normalize `approval_state` before calling
+  `build_preview_payload(...)` so `manual_review` becomes
+  `human_review_required` for both live and fallback preview responses.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: keep `approval_state` and
+  `requires_human_review` in the fallback `preview_unavailable` payload.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: add regression coverage for
+  `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
+  and assert the fallback payload preserves
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` plus
+  `requires_human_review=true`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: update the fallback payload example and notes to
+  match the fixed behavior.
+
+## Verification
+
+- Targeted tests to run:
+  - `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router`
+- Expected fallback behavior:
+  - `status = "preview_unavailable"`
+  - `approval_state = "human_review_required"`
+  - `requires_human_review = true`
+
+## Notes
+
+- No legacy preview branch or hint logic was reintroduced.
+- `thread_digest.md` was not used as authority; the exported JSON thread list was
+  treated as the source of truth.
