+# PR 214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py`. The fallback payload now keeps both
+`approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled=False`, so
+the reopened preview-unavailable path preserves the policy signal.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Classified as a duplicate of `T-214-01`. It describes the same reopened fallback
+payload regression, so no separate code path or additional patch was needed.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This comment points at an outdated hunk and suggests reviving
+legacy preview branching. The current branch should not reintroduce legacy
+preview-hint behavior, so the remediation keeps the current path and fixes the
+active fallback regression instead.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Fixed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression test that routes
+`approval_state="manual_review"` through `build_policy_preview(...)` with
+`preview_enabled=False` and asserts the normalized fallback response keeps
+`approval_state="human_review_required"` plus
+`requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Fixed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback example now matches the
+corrected payload and includes `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and
+`requires_human_review: true`.
